Stories:

- Only install on Solaris

- Determine if module is loaded or not
  ::dmod <modname>; loaded and not loaded

* Determine if variable is defined or not
  Solaris::mdb::Variable (attribute?)

- Determine size (in bytes) of an existing variable
  Solaris::mdb::Variable attribute, initialized at construction time

- Allow setting preferred output format for a variable
  Solaris::mdb::Variable attribute

- Print variable in variety of formats (dec, hex, oct, binary),

- Run a command, dcmd, walker, pipeline, and pass a code reference to work
  with the output
